Joe Anderson, 56, claimed £4,500 per year from Chesterfield High School, Merseyside .
He was a senior learning mentor at the school from 2001 until 2011 .
But when school became academy in 2011, he tried to sue them .
Judge ruled that he was unfairly dismissed and that school was right to stop payments .
Mr Anderson, who is paid an £80,000 salary, said he was being punished for his 'philosophical belief' in public service .